Paper: hep-th/9204065

Date: 1992-04-21

Title: Field-Antifield formalism for Anomalous Gauge Theories

Authors: Joaquim Gomis and Jordi Par\'{\i}s

Comments: 41 pages

Journal-ref: Nucl.Phys. B395 (1993) 288-324

An extension of the Field-Antifield formalism to treat anomalous gaugetheories with a closed, irreducible classical gauge algebra is proposed.Introducing extra degrees of freedom, we construct the gauge transformationsfor these new fields, the Wess-Zumino term and the corresponding measure.